quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,70,"If We willed, We verily could make it salt (and undrinkable): why then do you not give thanks (to Allâh)?"
  56,71,"Then tell Me about the fire which you kindle."
  56,72,"Is it you who made the tree thereof to grow, or are We the Grower?"
  67,10,"And they will say: "
  67,11,"Then they will confess their sin. So, away with the dwellers of the blazing Fire!"
  67,12,"Verily,, those who fear their Lord unseen (i.e. they do not see Him, nor His punishment in the Hereafter), theirs will be forgiveness and a great reward (i.e. Paradise)."
  68,4,"And Verily, you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) are on an exalted (standard of) character."
  68,5,"You will see, and they will see,"
  68,6,"Which of you is afflicted with madness."
  69,1,"The Inevitable (i.e. the Day of Resurrection)!"
  69,2,"What is the Inevitable?"
  69,3,"And what will make you know what the Inevitable is?"